# CustomerVoice Implementation Plan (Phases 1-6, Code-Aligned)

Last updated: 2026-03-07

## 1. Purpose and Scope
This document is the detailed implementation record for CustomerVoice Phases 1-6.
It is based on the current codebase state in:
- `apps/api`
- `apps/web`
- `apps/worker`
- `apps/e2e`

Roadmap labels come from `docs/CustomerVoice-Phases.md`.
This document explains what is implemented, how it is implemented, and what boundaries still exist.

## 2. Source of Truth
- Roadmap labels: `docs/CustomerVoice-Phases.md`
- Phase summary: `docs/summary.md`
- This detailed implementation record: `docs/implementation_plan.md.resolved`

## 3. Platform Baseline
### 3.1 Runtime architecture
- Monorepo: Turborepo
- Backend API: Node.js + Express + PostgreSQL (`apps/api`)
- Frontend apps: React + Vite + TypeScript (`apps/web`)
- Worker: Node.js notification/webhook dispatcher (`apps/worker`)
- E2E: Playwright (`apps/e2e`)

### 3.2 API surface split
- Public/no actor routes: `publicRouter`, `ssoRouter`
- Authenticated actor routes: `boardsRouter`, `ideasRouter`, `membersRouter`, `auditRouter`, `webhooksRouter`, `ssoConnectionsRouter`
- Auth model: `AUTH_MODE=mock` (header actor) or Supabase JWT validation

### 3.3 Database migration baseline
Implemented migrations (in `apps/api/src/db/migrations.ts`):
- `001_initial_schema`
- `002_boards_schema`
- `003_ideas_schema`
- `004_v1_portal_polish_schema`
- `005_portal_access_and_engagement`
- `006_engagement_features`
- `007_platform_excellence`
- `008_auth_notifications`
- `009_idea_attachments`
- `010_idea_merging`
- `011_internal_staff_comments`
- `012_mrr_tracking`
- `013_enterprise_sso`

## 4. Phase 1: Core Portal
Goal: Public feedback portal with auth, idea submission, voting, comments, and board access controls.

### 4.1 Product capabilities implemented
- Public board + settings retrieval
- Public idea list/detail view
- Email/password auth: register, login, me, logout
- Idea submission from public portal
- Voting and unvoting
- Comment posting
- Board-level access and interaction settings (auth requirements + toggles)

### 4.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `001_initial_schema`: tenants/workspaces/users/memberships/permissions/audit
- `002_boards_schema`: boards
- `003_ideas_schema`: ideas/votes/comments
- `005_portal_access_and_engagement`: `board_settings`, `portal_users`, `portal_sessions`

### 4.3 API implementation
Core public routes in `apps/api/src/routes/public.ts`:
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug`
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/settings`
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas`
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId`
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/categories`
- `POST /public/auth/register`
- `POST /public/auth/login`
- `GET /public/auth/me`
- `POST /public/auth/logout`
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas`
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/votes`
- `DELETE /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/votes`
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/comments`

### 4.4 Frontend implementation
`apps/web/src/CustomerPortal.tsx`:
- Board shell + filters + idea cards + detail panel/page
- Auth modal and session persistence
- Submit idea modal with validation
- Vote/comment flows gated by board settings

`apps/web/src/AdminDashboard.tsx` and `apps/api/src/routes/boards.ts`:
- Board settings updates for access/auth/visibility/branding toggles

### 4.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete (Phase 1 baseline delivered and running)

## 5. Phase 2: Enhanced UX and Retention
Goal: Better user identity, retention workflows, and high-volume usability.

### 5.1 Product capabilities implemented
- User profile read/update
- Idea follow/subscription
- Idea favorites
- Official/team comment flags
- Paginated public idea browsing (limit/offset + load more behavior)

### 5.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `006_engagement_features`:
  - `idea_subscriptions`
  - `idea_favorites`
  - `is_official`, `is_team_member` on `idea_comments`

### 5.3 API implementation
Public routes in `apps/api/src/routes/public.ts`:
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/subscribe`
- `DELETE /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/subscribe`
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/favorite`
- `DELETE /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/favorite`
- `GET /public/me/profile`
- `PATCH /public/me/profile`
- `GET /public/me/subscriptions`
- `GET /public/me/favorites`
- `GET /public/me/ideas`
- `GET /public/me/votes`

### 5.4 Frontend implementation
`apps/web/src/CustomerPortal.tsx`:
- Favorite toggles on cards + detail
- Follow toggle on idea detail
- User dropdown + profile context
- Incremental idea list pagination (`limit`, `offset`, `loadMoreIdeas`)

### 5.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete for documented Phase 2 scope

## 6. Phase 3: Platform Excellence
Goal: Rich roadmap/changelog communication and stronger discussion UX.

### 6.1 Product capabilities implemented
- Public roadmap tab by status columns
- Public changelog listing
- Threaded comments and comment upvotes
- Markdown rendering in idea/comment content
- Board branding controls (title, colors, logo, header styling, powered-by toggle)

### 6.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `007_platform_excellence`:
  - `changelog_entries`
  - `parent_comment_id`, `upvote_count` on comments
  - `comment_upvotes`
  - branding fields in `board_settings`

### 6.3 API implementation
Public routes in `apps/api/src/routes/public.ts`:
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/changelog`
- `POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/comments/:commentId/upvote`
- `DELETE /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId/comments/:commentId/upvote`
- Threaded view via `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas/:ideaId?threaded=true`

Admin route in `apps/api/src/routes/boards.ts`:
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/boards/:boardId/changelogs`

### 6.4 Frontend implementation
`apps/web/src/CustomerPortal.tsx`:
- Tabs: ideas/roadmap/changelog
- Markdown rendering via `react-markdown` + `remark-gfm`
- Thread building from flat comment payload

`apps/web/src/AdminDashboard.tsx`:
- Changelog publish UI for board admins

### 6.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete for documented Phase 3 scope

## 7. Phase 4: Admin, Auth, Notifications, Attachments
Goal: Internal operations UI, richer auth paths, async notifications, and files.

### 7.1 Product capabilities implemented
- Admin board and idea operations UI
- Password reset flow (request + reset)
- Social auth mock flow (GitHub/Google callback simulation)
- Worker-driven notification dispatch
- Idea/comment file attachments

### 7.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `008_auth_notifications`: relaxed nullability for non-idea auth jobs
- `009_idea_attachments`: `idea_attachments`, `comment_attachments`
- `007_platform_excellence`: `password_reset_tokens`

### 7.3 API implementation
Auth and password reset routes in `apps/api/src/routes/public.ts`:
- `POST /public/auth/forgot-password`
- `POST /public/auth/reset-password`
- `GET /public/auth/:provider`
- `GET /public/auth/:provider/callback`

Attachment routes in `apps/api/src/routes/public.ts` and `apps/api/src/routes/ideas.ts`:
- Public submit attachment routes for ideas/comments
- Internal idea/comment attachment routes for workspace users

### 7.4 Worker implementation
`apps/worker/src/index.ts`:
- Polls `notification_jobs` and claims with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`
- Sends email via SMTP (`nodemailer`)
- Handles templates:
  - `auth.reset_password`
  - `analytics.outreach`
  - default completion notification
- Dispatches matching webhooks once per job attempt cycle

### 7.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete for Phase 4 baseline
- Note: OAuth provider flow is currently mock/simulated, not full external provider handshake

## 8. Phase 5: Moderation and Integrations
Goal: Strong moderation controls and external event integrations.

### 8.1 Product capabilities implemented
- Idea merge workflows (board-scoped)
- Spam and comment-lock moderation actions
- Bulk moderation actions
- Internal comments (staff-only note behavior)
- Webhook CRUD and worker webhook dispatch
- Internal analytics and outreach operations (implemented operational extension)

### 8.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `004_v1_portal_polish_schema`: moderation columns + analytics inputs + notification jobs
- `010_idea_merging`: legacy `merged_into_id` compatibility column
- `011_internal_staff_comments`: `is_internal` on comments
- `007_platform_excellence`: `webhooks`

### 8.3 API implementation
Moderation/analytics routes in `apps/api/src/routes/ideas.ts`:
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/boards/:boardId/ideas/:ideaId/merge`
- `GET /workspaces/:workspaceId/moderation/ideas`
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/moderation/ideas/merge`
- `PATCH /workspaces/:workspaceId/moderation/ideas/:ideaId/spam`
- `PATCH /workspaces/:workspaceId/moderation/ideas/:ideaId/comments-lock`
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/moderation/ideas/bulk`
- `GET /workspaces/:workspaceId/analytics/ideas`
- `PUT /workspaces/:workspaceId/analytics/ideas/:ideaId/input`
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/analytics/ideas/:ideaId/outreach`

Webhook routes in `apps/api/src/routes/webhooks.ts`:
- `GET /workspaces/:workspaceId/webhooks`
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/webhooks`
- `PATCH /workspaces/:workspaceId/webhooks/:webhookId`
- `DELETE /workspaces/:workspaceId/webhooks/:webhookId`

### 8.4 Frontend implementation
`apps/web/src/PortalApp.tsx`:
- Moderation queue and actions
- Merge UI for source->target idea merge
- Analytics panel with scoring and outreach dispatch

`apps/web/src/AdminDashboard.tsx`:
- Webhook management panel

### 8.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete for Phase 5 baseline

## 9. Phase 6: Real-Time and Enterprise Scale
Goal: Live UX, enterprise identity baseline, revenue impact inputs, and E2E quality gate.

### 9.1 Product capabilities implemented
- SSE live updates for votes/comments
- Widget mode rendering for embedded usage (`?widget=true` compact UI mode)
- MRR tracking and impact-driven sorting
- Enterprise SSO login/callback baseline and workspace SSO connection management
- Deterministic Playwright E2E gate for core portal + SSO flows

### 9.2 Data model and migrations
Primary schema pieces:
- `012_mrr_tracking`: `portal_users.mrr`
- `013_enterprise_sso`: `sso_connections`

### 9.3 API implementation
SSE and impact sorting:
- `GET /public/boards/:boardSlug/stream`
- Public idea sort includes `highest_impact`
- MRR sync endpoint: `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/users/mrr`

SSO routes:
- `GET /auth/sso/login`
- `ALL /auth/sso/callback`
- `GET /workspaces/:workspaceId/sso-connections`
- `POST /workspaces/:workspaceId/sso-connections`
- `PATCH /workspaces/:workspaceId/sso-connections/:connectionId`

### 9.4 Frontend and test implementation
`apps/web/src/CustomerPortal.tsx`:
- EventSource subscription updates list/detail state in real time
- `highest_impact` sort option exposed in portal UI
- Widget mode classing/styling path

`apps/e2e`:
- Playwright config aligned to `web:3333`, `api:4000`
- `sso.spec.ts` validates SSO redirect/callback token flow
- `portal-phase6.spec.ts` validates register -> submit -> vote -> comment core flow

### 9.5 Completion status
- Status: Complete for Phase 6 baseline
- Current boundary: SSO is production-baseline but still mock-prototype style in parts (dynamic provider hardening and full IdP lifecycle workflows remain post-Phase-6 work)
- Current boundary: Widget support is currently widget mode in portal UX, not a full standalone JS SDK distribution package

## 10. Quality and Validation Baseline
Latest validated gates:
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/api typecheck`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/web typecheck`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/e2e typecheck`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/api test:integration`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/api test:integration:db`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/e2e test:e2e`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/api lint`
- `pnpm --filter @customervoice/web lint`

## 11. Implementation Readiness for Phase 7
With Phases 1-6 baseline complete and blocker suites green, the system is ready for the locked Phase 7 execution track.
Phase 7 is now the true multi-tenant foundation program, with enterprise-domain tenant resolution, personal-tenant handling for public-email users, tenant-aware auth/session/routing, and migration cutover defined in `docs/CustomerVoice-Phase7-Planning.md`.
